<Window x:Class="ClientGUI.AboutPage"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:ClientGUI"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="About" Height="349" Width="388" ResizeMode="NoResize">
    <Grid>
        <TextBlock x:Name="label" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="10" TextWrapping="Wrap">
            This is client of InfoServer, where you can view, create, udpate and delete cards. <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            Make sure the server is running, otherwise none operations will work. <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            First, load all cards from server using InfoClient's "Load cards" menu button. It loads all cards from server and display them. <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            To create new card, click InfoClient's "New card" menu button. It shows Card window where you must input name (into Name field) and choose image (using button) and then click "Save". <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            To edit existing cards, click on it in InfoClient window. It opens this card's window where you can change name or image. <LineBreak/> Then, if you want to save - click "Save" button, 
            if you don't want to save - click "Return button", if you want to delete (both from client and server) this card - click "Delete" button.
        </TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</Window>
